1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,284
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:00:08,284 --> 00:00:11,320
[Episode Thirty-six]

3
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:14,560
I heard that the Chinese have organized death squads.

4
00:00:13,638 --> 00:00:16,225
[Wang Zhengting, styled Rutang, Plenipotentiary of the Southern Government]

5
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:16,960
Three people for a minister's life.

6
00:00:17,425 --> 00:00:19,663
[Gu Weiju, styled Shaochuan, Ambassador to the United States]

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,600
Thousands of people signed up.

8
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:21,760
Qingdao is ours!

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,240
Qingdao is ours!

10
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,760
Shandong is ours!

11
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:29,280
I really want to go down

12
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,040
and tell them what I think.

13
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:36,160
Don't go out today or tomorrow.

14
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:39,840
Once you go out, you will be killed.

15
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,240
Don't worry. Chief Lu is waiting for a telegram.

16
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:46,720
If it's a signed telegram,

17
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,720
Rutang,

18
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:51,120
Refuse to sign the Paris Peace Treaty!

19
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:52,880
I'll go out with you and make a statement.

20
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,680
Refuse to sign the Paris Treaty!

21
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,280
Refuse to sign the Paris Treaty!

22
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:57,840
Okay.

23
00:00:58,720 --> 00:00:59,840
Today I'm ready

24
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:02,240
to spill my blood to Paris.

25
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:14,000
Refuse to sign the Paris Peace Treaty!

26
00:01:26,672 --> 00:01:29,761
[Lu Zhengxiang, styled Zixin, Head of the Chinese delegation at the Paris Peace Conference]

27
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,280
Gentlemen,

28
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:34,240
it's almost time to sign the treaty.

29
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,280
It's evening in Beijing.

30
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,280
The government has already left work.

31
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,080
Until now,

32
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:46,080
I have not received any clear instructions

33
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,800
from the government to sign or not to sign.

34
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,640
In other words,

35
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:56,160
we have to go our own way.

36
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:02,160
Zixin, what are your plans?

37
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:03,440
Go ahead.

38
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:10,800
Shaochuan, I want to hear your opinion first.

39
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,520
My opinion is simple.

40
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,720
Even if the government insists,

41
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,560
I will never sign it.

42
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,400
Rutang,

43
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,080
what about you?

44
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,680
I am no different from Shaochuan.

45
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:34,720
Good.

46
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,240
Good.

47
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,040
Gentlemen,

48
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,080
what do you think?

49
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,440
Never sign.

50
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:50,000
I drafted two statements.

51
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,520
The first one is for China.

52
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,600
The message is as follows:

53
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,320
After detailed review and discussion,

54
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,240
we have no choice but to sign.

55
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:09,280
The second is for the Paris Peace Conference.

56
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,520
We declare to not sign.

57
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,000
If you have no objection,

58
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,000
I'll ask the Secretary General

59
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,920
to deliver these.

60
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:08,320
28 June 1919,

61
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,240
Under the tremendous pressure

62
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:13,040
of the continuous mass protests of the entire Chinese people

63
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,080
and the unprecedented patriotic enthusiasm

64
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,400
of the whole nation for national salvation,

65
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,080
the Chinese delegation

66
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,040
finally

67
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:24,320
refused to sign the humiliating Paris Peace Treaty.

68
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,600
This is an important achievement

69
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:29,040
of the May Fourth Patriotic Movement

70
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,720
a victory in the history of Chinese diplomacy

71
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,840
since the Opium War.

72
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,040
This victory

73
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:37,520
is the result of the national people's unity and heroic struggle

74
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,760
against imperialism and the Beiyang government,

75
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,760
an important symbol

76
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:44,880
of the great awakening

77
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,800
of the Chinese nation.

78
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,560
Until February 1922,

79
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,040
China and Japan signed

80
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:57,120
the "Treaty on the Settlement of Unsolved Cases in Shandong" and its Appendices

81
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,560
The Shandong problem has been solved to some extent,

82
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:04,480
but Japan continues to maintain considerable power

83
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:08,240
in Shandong.

84
00:05:10,032 --> 00:05:15,111
[Changsha, Hunan]

85
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,280
The time has come.

86
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,160
The world's tide is rolling more dramatically.

87
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:23,760
The gate of Dongting Lake moved and opened.

88
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,760
A mighty new trend of thought

89
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:29,440
has surged on both sides of Xiangjiang River.

90
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,360
Follow its life

91
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,040
